React Optimizations
âœ… 1. Lazy loading components:
What? Used React.lazy() and Suspense to dynamically import the About page.
Benefit? The About page doesnt load on the initial render, reducing the JavaScript bundle size.
Code Used:
const About = lazy(() => import("./components/About"));
<Suspense fallback={<h2>Loading...</h2>}>
<About />
</Suspense>

âœ… 2. Code splitting using route based splitting:
What? We split our React app into multiple chunks so that unnecessary code isnt downloaded until needed.
Benefit? Faster initial load time as only the Home page is loaded initially.
Code Used:
Webpack will handle this split automatically when using React.lazy().

âœ… 3. Using CSS modules scoped styles:
What? Created Home.module.css and About.module.css instead of global styles.
Benefit? Prevents CSS conflicts, improves maintainability, and allows Webpack to optimize unused CSS.
Code Used:
import styles from "./Home.module.css";

âœ… 4. Tree Shaking (Eliminating Unused Code)
What? Webpack removes unused code (like parts of libraries not imported).
Benefit? Reduces bundle size significantly.
Example: If we import only one function from Lodash instead of the whole library:
import { debounce } from "lodash-es";
Without tree shaking: Entire Lodash library would be bundled.
With tree shaking: Only debounce is included in the final bundle.

âœ… 5. Lazy Loading External Libraries (Lodash)
What? Instead of bundling Lodash with the initial JavaScript, we load it only when needed.
Benefit? Reduces initial JavaScript size, improving page load speed.
Code Used:
import("lodash").then(({ debounce }) => {
console.log("Lodash loaded lazily!");
});
Lodash will be dynamically imported only on demand, keeping the main bundle smaller.

âœ… 7. Output Optimization (Caching & Content Hashing)
What? Webpack generates hashed filenames for caching.
Benefit? Browsers cache files efficiently without loading outdated versions.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
output: {
filename: "[name].[contenthash].js",
}

âœ… 8. SplitChunks (Vendor & Runtime Code Splitting)
What? Webpack separates vendor libraries (e.g., React, Lodash) from app code.
Benefit? Browser caches vendor libraries separately, reducing redundant downloads.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
optimization: {
splitChunks: {
chunks: "all",
},
}
Result?
vendors~main.[hash].js â†’ Common dependencies (e.g., React, Lodash)
main.[hash].js â†’ App-specific code

âœ… 9. Minification & Compression
What? Webpack minifies JavaScript & CSS for smaller file sizes.
Benefit? Reduces file size by ~50% for faster load times.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
optimization: {
minimize: true,
minimizer: [
new TerserPlugin(),
new CssMinimizerPlugin(),
],
}

âœ… 10. Babel Loader (Modern JavaScript Optimization)
What? Uses Babel to transpile modern JavaScript (ES6+) into older versions for browser compatibility.
Benefit? Ensures code runs smoothly across all browsers.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
module: {
rules: [
{
test: /\.js$/,
exclude: /node_modules/,
use: {
loader: "babel-loader",
},
},
],
},

âœ… 11. Image Optimization
What? Webpack optimizes and compresses images.
Benefit? Faster page loads & reduced bandwidth usage.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
module: {
rules: [
{
test: /\.(png|jpg|jpeg|gif)$/i,
type: "asset/resource",
},
],
},

âœ… 12. CSS Extraction (Optimized CSS Loading)
What? Extracts CSS into separate files.
Benefit? Browser loads CSS files in parallel, improving performance.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
plugins: [
new MiniCssExtractPlugin({
filename: "[name].[contenthash].css",
}),
],

âœ… 13. Using Source Maps for Debugging
What? Generates source maps for easier debugging in development mode.
Benefit? Errors point to the original source file, not minified code.
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
devtool: "source-map",

âœ… 14. Development & Production Mode Separation
What? Used mode: "production" & mode: "development".
Benefit?
Development: Fast builds, source maps enabled
Production: Minified code, optimized assets
Code Used (webpack.config.js):
mode: process.env.NODE_ENV === "production" ? "production" : "development"

